messages.translation: 列出組織中的所有使用者。僅當您是具有管理專用權的使用者時才能這樣做。

messages.id: When listing all of the users, show only the usernames, instead of each entire resource.
messages.message: When listing all of the users, show only the usernames, instead of each entire resource.
messages.translation: 當列出所有使用者時，只會顯示使用者名稱而不是每個使用者的整個資源。

messages.id: Remove a user resource from the Horizon Exchange. Warning: this will cause all exchange resources owned by this user to also be deleted (nodes, services, patterns, etc).
messages.message: Remove a user resource from the Horizon Exchange. Warning: this will cause all exchange resources owned by this user to also be deleted (nodes, services, patterns, etc).
messages.translation: 從 Horizon Exchange 中移除使用者資源。 警告：這樣做還會導致刪除此使用者擁有的所有 Exchange 資源（節點、服務、型樣等）。

messages.id: The user to remove.
messages.message: The user to remove.
messages.translation: 要移除的使用者。

messages.id: Change the existing user to be an admin user (like root in his/her org) or to no longer be an admin user. Can only be run by exchange root or another admin user.
messages.message: Change the existing user to be an admin user (like root in his/her org) or to no longer be an admin user. Can only be run by exchange root or another admin user.
messages.translation: 將現有使用者變更為管理使用者（例如其組織內的 root 使用者）或變更為非管理使用者。 只有 Exchange root 使用者或其他管理使用者才能執行此動作。

messages.id: The user to be modified.
messages.message: The user to be modified.
messages.translation: 要修改的使用者。

messages.id: True if they should be an admin user, otherwise false.
messages.message: True if they should be an admin user, otherwise false.
messages.translation: 如果他們應該為管理使用者，則為 True，否則為 False。

messages.id: Display the version of the Horizon Exchange.
messages.message: Display the version of the Horizon Exchange.
messages.translation: 顯示 Horizon Exchange 的版本。

messages.id: List and manage keys for signing and verifying services.
messages.message: List and manage keys for signing and verifying services.
messages.translation: 列出並管理用於簽署及驗證服務的金鑰。

messages.id: Generate a signing key pair.
messages.message: Generate a signing key pair.
messages.translation: 產生簽署金鑰組。

messages.id: x509 certificate Organization (O) field (preferably a company name or other organization's name).
messages.message: x509 certificate Organization (O) field (preferably a company name or other organization's name).
messages.translation: x509 憑證組織 (O) 欄位（最好是公司名稱或其他組織的名稱）。

messages.id: x509 certificate Common Name (CN) field (preferably an email address issued by x509org).
messages.message: x509 certificate Common Name (CN) field (preferably an email address issued by x509org).
messages.translation: x509 憑證通用名稱 (CN) 欄位（最好是由 x509org 簽發的電子郵件位址）。

messages.id: The directory to put the key pair files in. Mutually exclusive with -k and -K. The file names will be randomly generated.
messages.message: The directory to put the key pair files in. Mutually exclusive with -k and -K. The file names will be randomly generated.
messages.translation: 放置金鑰組檔案的目錄。 與 -k 和 -K 互斥。 檔名將隨機產生。

messages.id: The full path of the private key file. Mutually exclusive with -d. If not specified, the environment variable HZN_PRIVATE_KEY_FILE will be used. If none of them are set, ~/.hzn/keys/service.private.key is the default.
messages.message: The full path of the private key file. Mutually exclusive with -d. If not specified, the environment variable HZN_PRIVATE_KEY_FILE will be used. If none of them are set, ~/.hzn/keys/service.private.key is the default.
messages.translation: 私密金鑰檔的完整路徑。 與 -d 互斥。 如果未指定，則將會使用環境變數 HZN_PRIVATE_KEY_FILE。 如果未設定任何一項，則 ~/.hzn/keys/service.private.key 是預設值。

messages.id: The full path of the public key file. Mutually exclusive with -d. If not specified, the environment variable HZN_PUBLIC_KEY_FILE will be used. If none of them are set, ~/.hzn/keys/service.public.pem is the default.
messages.message: The full path of the public key file. Mutually exclusive with -d. If not specified, the environment variable HZN_PUBLIC_KEY_FILE will be used. If none of them are set, ~/.hzn/keys/service.public.pem is the default.
messages.translation: 公開金鑰檔的完整路徑。 與 -d 互斥。 如果未指定，則將會使用環境變數 HZN_PUBLIC_KEY_FILE。 如果未設定任何一項，則 ~/.hzn/keys/service.public.pem 是預設值。

messages.id: Overwrite the existing files. It will skip the 'do you want to overwrite' prompt.
messages.message: Overwrite the existing files. It will skip the 'do you want to overwrite' prompt.
messages.translation: 改寫現有檔案。 它將會跳過「要改寫嗎」提示。

messages.id: The length of the key to create.
messages.message: The length of the key to create.
messages.translation: 要建立之金鑰的長度。

messages.id: x509 certificate validity (Validity > Not After) expressed in days from the day of generation.
messages.message: x509 certificate validity (Validity > Not After) expressed in days from the day of generation.
messages.translation: x509 憑證有效性（有效性 > 有效終止日期），以天數表示（從產生之日起計算）。

messages.id: Automatically import the created public key into the local Horizon agent.
messages.message: Automatically import the created public key into the local Horizon agent.
messages.translation: 自動將建立的公開金鑰匯入至本端 Horizon 代理程式。

messages.id: Imports a signing public key into the Horizon agent.
messages.message: Imports a signing public key into the Horizon agent.
messages.translation: 將簽署公開金鑰匯入至 Horizon 代理程式。

messages.id: The path of a pem public key file to be imported. The base name in the path is also used as the key name in the Horizon agent. If not specified, the environment variable HZN_PUBLIC_KEY_FILE will be used. If none of them are set, ~/.hzn/keys/service.public.pem is the default.
messages.message: The path of a pem public key file to be imported. The base name in the path is also used as the key name in the Horizon agent. If not specified, the environment variable HZN_PUBLIC_KEY_FILE will be used. If none of them are set, ~/.hzn/keys/service.public.pem is the default.
messages.translation: 要匯入之 pem 公開金鑰檔的路徑。 路徑中的基本名稱也會用來作為 Horizon 代理程式中的金鑰名稱。 如果未指定，則將會使用環境變數 HZN_PUBLIC_KEY_FILE。 如果未設定任何一項，則 ~/.hzn/keys/service.public.pem 是預設值。

messages.id: List the signing keys that have been imported into this Horizon agent.
messages.message: List the signing keys that have been imported into this Horizon agent.
messages.translation: 列出已匯入至此 Horizon 代理程式的簽署金鑰。

messages.id: The name of a specific key to show.
messages.message: The name of a specific key to show.
messages.translation: 要顯示之特定金鑰的名稱。

messages.id: List the names of all signing keys, even the older public keys not wrapped in a certificate.
messages.message: List the names of all signing keys, even the older public keys not wrapped in a certificate.
messages.translation: 列出所有簽署金鑰的名稱，甚至包含在憑證中未覆蓋的較舊公開金鑰。

messages.id: Remove the specified signing key from this Horizon agent.
messages.message: Remove the specified signing key from this Horizon agent.
messages.translation: 從 Horizon 代理程式中移除指定的簽署金鑰。

messages.id: The name of a specific key to remove.
messages.message: The name of a specific key to remove.
messages.translation: 要移除之特定金鑰的名稱。

messages.id: List or manage the metering (payment) information for the active or archived agreements.
messages.message: List or manage the metering (payment) information for the active or archived agreements.
messages.translation: 列出或管理作用中合約或保存合約的計量（付款）資訊。

messages.id: List the metering (payment) information for the active or archived agreements.
messages.message: List the metering (payment) information for the active or archived agreements.
messages.translation: 列出作用中合約或保存合約的計量（付款）資訊。

messages.id: List archived agreement metering information instead of metering for the active agreements.
messages.message: List archived agreement metering information instead of metering for the active agreements.
messages.translation: 列出保存合約計量資訊而非作用中合約的計量資訊。

messages.id: List and manage Horizon Model Management Service resources.
messages.message: List and manage Horizon Model Management Service resources.
messages.translation: 列出並管理 Horizon 模型管理服務資源。

messages.id: The Horizon organization ID. If not specified, HZN_ORG_ID will be used as a default.
messages.message: The Horizon organization ID. If not specified, HZN_ORG_ID will be used as a default.
messages.translation: Horizon 組織 ID。 如果未指定，則將使用 HZN_ORG_ID 作為預設值。

messages.id: Horizon user credentials to query and create Model Management Service resources. If not specified, HZN_EXCHANGE_USER_AUTH will be used as a default. If you don't prepend it with the user's org, it will automatically be prepended with the -o value.
messages.message: Horizon user credentials to query and create Model Management Service resources. If not specified, HZN_EXCHANGE_USER_AUTH will be used as a default. If you don't prepend it with the user's org, it will automatically be prepended with the -o value.
messages.translation: 用來查詢並建立模型管理服務資源的 Horizon 使用者認證。 如果未指定，則將使用 HZN_EXCHANGE_USER_AUTH 作為預設值。 如果您未在它前面加上使用者的組織，則它前面會自動加上 -o 值。

messages.id: List and manage objects in the Horizon Model Management Service.
messages.message: List and manage objects in the Horizon Model Management Service.
messages.translation: 列出並管理 Horizon 模型管理服務的物件。

messages.id: Delete an object in the Horizon Model Management Service, making it unavailable for services deployed on nodes.
messages.message: Delete an object in the Horizon Model Management Service, making it unavailable for services deployed on nodes.
messages.translation: 刪除 Horizon 模型管理服務中的物件，使其無法用於節點上部署的服務。

messages.id: The type of the object to delete.
messages.message: The type of the object to delete.
messages.translation: 要刪除之物件的類型。

messages.id: The id of the object to delete.
messages.message: The id of the object to delete.
messages.translation: 要刪除之物件的 ID。

messages.id: Download data of the given object in the Horizon Model Management Service.
messages.message: Download data of the given object in the Horizon Model Management Service.
messages.translation: 下載 Horizon 模型管理服務中給定物件的資料。

messages.id: The type of the object to download data. This flag must be used with -i.
messages.message: The type of the object to download data. This flag must be used with -i.
messages.translation: 要下載其資料的物件類型。 此旗標必須與 -i 搭配使用。

messages.id: The id of the object to download data. This flag must be used with -t.
messages.message: The id of the object to download data. This flag must be used with -t.
messages.translation: 要下載其資料的物件 ID。 此旗標必須與 -t 搭配使用。

messages.id: The file that the data of downloaded object is written to. This flag must be used with -f. If omit, will use default file name in format of objectType_objectID and save in current directory
messages.message: The file that the data of downloaded object is written to. This flag must be used with -f. If omit, will use default file name in format of objectType_objectID and save in current directory
messages.translation: 將在其中寫入所下載物件之資料的檔案。 此旗標必須與 -f 搭配使用。 如果省略，將使用格式為 objectType_objectID 的預設檔案名稱並儲存在現行目錄中

messages.id: Overwrite the existing file if it exists in the file system.
messages.message: Overwrite the existing file if it exists in the file system.
messages.translation: 如果現有檔案存在於檔案系統中，請改寫它。

messages.id: The download command will not perform a data integrity check on the downloaded object data
messages.message: The download command will not perform a data integrity check on the downloaded object data
messages.translation: 下載指令將不會對下載的物件資料執行資料完整性檢查

messages.id: List objects in the Horizon Model Management Service.
messages.message: List objects in the Horizon Model Management Service.
messages.translation: 列出 Horizon 模型管理服務中的物件。

messages.id: The type of the object to list.
messages.message: The type of the object to list.
messages.translation: 要列出之物件的類型。

messages.id: The id of the object to list. This flag is optional. Omit this flag to list all objects of a given object type.
messages.message: The id of the object to list. This flag is optional. Omit this flag to list all objects of a given object type.
messages.translation: 要列出之物件的類 ID。 這是選用旗標。 省略此旗標會列出給定物件類型的所有物件。

messages.id: Specify true to show only objects using policy. Specify false to show only objects not using policy. If this flag is omitted, both kinds of objects are shown.
messages.message: Specify true to show only objects using policy. Specify false to show only objects not using policy. If this flag is omitted, both kinds of objects are shown.
messages.translation: 指定 true 以僅顯示使用原則的物件。 指定 false 以僅顯示未使用原則的物件。 如果省略此旗標，則會顯示兩種類型的物件。

messages.id: List mms objects using policy that are targetted for the given service. Service specified in the format service-org/service-name.
messages.message: List mms objects using policy that are targetted for the given service. Service specified in the format service-org/service-name.
messages.translation: 列出使用原則且目標針對給定服務的 mms 服務。 以格式 service-org/service-name 指定的服務。

messages.id: List mms objects using policy that reference the given property name.
messages.message: List mms objects using policy that reference the given property name.
messages.translation: 列出使用原則且參照給定的內容名稱的 mms 物件。

messages.id: List mms objects using policy that has been updated since the given time. The time value is spefified in RFC3339 format: yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ssZ. The time of day may be omitted.
messages.message: List mms objects using policy that has been updated since the given time. The time value is spefified in RFC3339 format: yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ssZ. The time of day may be omitted.
messages.translation: 列出使用原則且自從給定時間以來更新的 mms 物件。 時間值以 RFC3339 格式 yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ssZ 指定。 可能會省略當天時間。

messages.id: List mms objects with given destination type
messages.message: List mms objects with given destination type
messages.translation: 列出具有給定目的地類型的 mms 物件

messages.id: List mms objects with given destination id. Must specify --destinationType to use this flag
messages.message: List mms objects with given destination id. Must specify --destinationType to use this flag
messages.translation: 列出具有給定目的地 ID 的 mms 物件。 必須指定 --destinationType 以使用此旗標

messages.id: Specify true to show objects that have data. Specify false to show objects that have no data. If this flag is omitted, both kinds of objects are shown.
messages.message: Specify true to show objects that have data. Specify false to show objects that have no data. If this flag is omitted, both kinds of objects are shown.
messages.translation: 指定 true 以顯示具有資料的物件。 指定 false 以顯示不含資料的物件。 如果省略此旗標，則會顯示兩種類型的物件。

messages.id: List mms objects that expired before the given time. The time value is spefified in RFC3339 format: yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ssZ. Specify now to show objects that are currently expired.
messages.message: List mms objects that expired before the given time. The time value is spefified in RFC3339 format: yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ssZ. Specify now to show objects that are currently expired.
messages.translation: 列出在給定時間之前過期的 mms 物件。 時間值以 RFC3339 格式 yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ssZ 指定。 指定現在以顯示目前過期的物件。

messages.id: Show detailed object metadata information
messages.message: Show detailed object metadata information
messages.translation: 顯示詳細的物件 Meta 資料資訊

messages.id: Provides additional detail about the deployment of the object on edge nodes.
messages.message: Provides additional detail about the deployment of the object on edge nodes.
messages.translation: 提供有關邊緣節點上物件部署的其他詳細資料。

messages.id: Display an empty object metadata template that can be filled in and passed as the -m option on the 'hzn mms object publish' command.
messages.message: Display an empty object metadata template that can be filled in and passed as the -m option on the 'hzn mms object publish' command.
messages.translation: 顯示可以填寫的空物件 meta 資料 範本，並將其作為 'hzn mms object publish' 指令上的 -m 選項傳遞。

messages.id: Publish an object in the Horizon Model Management Service, making it available for services deployed on nodes.
messages.message: Publish an object in the Horizon Model Management Service, making it available for services deployed on nodes.
messages.translation: 發佈 Horizon 模型管理服務中的物件，將其提供給節點上部署的服務。

messages.id: The type of the object to publish. This flag must be used with -i. It is mutually exclusive with -m
messages.message: The type of the object to publish. This flag must be used with -i. It is mutually exclusive with -m
messages.translation: 要發佈之物件的類型。 此旗標必須與 -i 搭配使用。 它與 -m 互斥

messages.id: The id of the object to publish. This flag must be used with -t. It is mutually exclusive with -m
messages.message: The id of the object to publish. This flag must be used with -t. It is mutually exclusive with -m
messages.translation: 要發佈之物件的 ID。 此旗標必須與 -t 搭配使用。 它與 -m 互斥

messages.id: If you want the object to be deployed on nodes using a given pattern, specify it using this flag. This flag is optional and can only be used with --type and --id. It is mutually exclusive with -m
messages.message: If you want the object to be deployed on nodes using a given pattern, specify it using this flag. This flag is optional and can only be used with --type and --id. It is mutually exclusive with -m
messages.translation: 若要在使用給定型樣的節點上部署物件，請使用此旗標來指定物件。 這是選用旗標，只能與 --type 和 --id 搭配使用。 它與 -m 互斥

messages.id: The definition of the object to publish. A blank template can be obtained from the 'hzn mss object new' command. Specify -m- to read from stdin.
messages.message: The definition of the object to publish. A blank template can be obtained from the 'hzn mss object new' command. Specify -m- to read from stdin.
messages.translation: 要發佈之物件的定義。 空白範本可透過 'hzn mss object new' 指令來獲取。 指定 -m- 以從 stdin 進行讀取。

messages.id: The object (in the form of a file) to publish. This flag is optional so that you can update only the object's definition.
messages.message: The object (in the form of a file) to publish. This flag is optional so that you can update only the object's definition.
messages.translation: 要發佈的物件（檔案格式）。 這是選用旗標，以便您可以僅更新物件的定義。

messages.id: The publish command will not perform a data integrity check on the uploaded object data. It is mutually exclusive with --hashAlgo and --hash
messages.message: The publish command will not perform a data integrity check on the uploaded object data. It is mutually exclusive with --hashAlgo and --hash
messages.translation: 發佈指令將不會對上傳的物件資料執行資料完整性檢查。 它與 --hashAlgo 和 --hash 互斥

messages.id: The hash algorithm used to hash the object data before signing it, ensuring data integrity during upload and download. Supported hash algorithms are SHA1 or SHA256, the default is SHA1. It is mutually exclusive with the --noIntegrity flag
messages.message: The hash algorithm used to hash the object data before signing it, ensuring data integrity during upload and download. Supported hash algorithms are SHA1 or SHA256, the default is SHA1. It is mutually exclusive with the --noIntegrity flag
messages.translation: 雜湊演算法用來在簽署物件資料之前對其進行混合，以確保上傳和下載期間的資料完整性。 支援的雜湊演算法為 SHA1 或 SHA256，預設值為 SHA1。 它與 --noIntegrity 旗標互斥

messages.id: The hash of the object data being uploaded or downloaded. Use this flag if you want to provide the hash instead of allowing the command to automatically calculate the hash. The hash must be generated using either the SHA1 or SHA256 algorithm. The -a flag must be specified if the hash was generated using SHA256. This flag is mutually exclusive with --noIntegrity.
messages.message: The hash of the object data being uploaded or downloaded. Use this flag if you want to provide the hash instead of allowing the command to automatically calculate the hash. The hash must be generated using either the SHA1 or SHA256 algorithm. The -a flag must be specified if the hash was generated using SHA256. This flag is mutually exclusive with --noIntegrity.
messages.translation: 所上傳或下載的物件資料的雜湊。 如果您想要提供雜湊，而不是容許指令自動計算雜湊，請使用此旗標。 必須使用 SHA1 或 SHA256 演算法產生雜湊。 如果是使用 SHA256 產生雜湊，則必須指定 -a 旗標。 此旗標與 --noIntegrity 互斥。

messages.id: The path of a private key file to be used to sign the object. The corresponding public key will be stored in the MMS to ensure integrity of the object. If not specified, the environment variable HZN_PRIVATE_KEY_FILE will be used to find a private key. If not set, ~/.hzn/keys/service.private.key will be used. If it does not exist, an RSA key pair is generated only for this publish operation and then the private key is discarded.
messages.message: The path of a private key file to be used to sign the object. The corresponding public key will be stored in the MMS to ensure integrity of the object. If not specified, the environment variable HZN_PRIVATE_KEY_FILE will be used to find a private key. If not set, ~/.hzn/keys/service.private.key will be used. If it does not exist, an RSA key pair is generated only for this publish operation and then the private key is discarded.
messages.translation: 要用來簽署物件之私密金鑰檔的路徑。 對應的公開金鑰將儲存在 MMS 中，以確保物件的完整性。 如果未指定，則將會使用環境變數 HZN_PRIVATE_KEY_FILE 來尋找私密金鑰。 如果未設定，則將使用 ~/.hzn/keys/service.private.key。 如果它不存在，則只會針對此發佈作業產生 RSA 金鑰組，私密金鑰隨後被捨棄。

messages.id: Display the status of the Horizon Model Management Service.
messages.message: Display the status of the Horizon Model Management Service.
messages.translation: 顯示 Horizon 模型管理服務的狀態。

messages.id: List and manage general information about this Horizon edge node.
messages.message: List and manage general information about this Horizon edge node.
messages.translation: 列出並管理關於這個 Horizon 邊緣節點的一般資訊。

messages.id: Display general information about this Horizon edge node.
messages.message: Display general information about this Horizon edge node.
messages.translation: 顯示關於這個 Horizon 邊緣節點的一般資訊。

messages.id: List and manage policy for this Horizon edge node.
messages.message: List and manage policy for this Horizon edge node.
messages.translation: 列出並管理這個 Horizon 邊緣節點的原則。

messages.id: Display this edge node's policy.
messages.message: Display this edge node's policy.
messages.translation: 顯示這個邊緣節點的原則。

messages.id: Display an empty policy template that can be filled in.
messages.message: Display an empty policy template that can be filled in.
messages.translation: 顯示可填寫的空原則範本。

messages.id: (DEPRECATED) This command is deprecated. Please use 'hzn policy update' to update the node policy. This command is used to update either the node policy properties or the constraints, but not both.
messages.message: (DEPRECATED) This command is deprecated. Please use 'hzn policy update' to update the node policy. This command is used to update either the node policy properties or the constraints, but not both.
messages.translation: （已淘汰）這個指令已淘汰。 請使用 'hzn policy update'，以更新節點原則。 此指令用來更新節點原則內容或限制，但不能同時更新兩者。

messages.id: The new constraints or properties in the format '{Constraintsconstraint_list}' or '{Propertiesproperty_list}'.
messages.message: The new constraints or properties in the format '{Constraintsconstraint_list}' or '{Propertiesproperty_list}'.
messages.translation: 格式為 '{Constraintsconstraint_list}' 或 '{Propertiesproperty_list}' 的新限制項或內容。

messages.id: Remove the node's policy.
messages.message: Remove the node's policy.
messages.translation: 移除節點的原則。

messages.id: Create or replace the node's policy. The node's built-in properties cannot be modified or deleted by this command, with the exception of openhorizon.allowPrivileged.
messages.message: Create or replace the node's policy. The node's built-in properties cannot be modified or deleted by this command, with the exception of openhorizon.allowPrivileged.
messages.translation: 建立或取代節點原則。 此指令無法修改或刪除節點的內建內容，異常狀況為 openhorizon.allowPrivileged。

messages.id: The JSON input file name containing the node policy. Specify -f- to read from stdin.
messages.message: The JSON input file name containing the node policy. Specify -f- to read from stdin.
messages.translation: 包含節點原則的 JSON 輸入檔名稱。 指定 -f- 以從 stdin 中讀取。

messages.id: Create an input file template for this pattern that can be used for the 'hzn register' command (once filled in). This examines the services that the specified pattern uses, and determines the node owner input that is required for them.
messages.message: Create an input file template for this pattern that can be used for the 'hzn register' command (once filled in). This examines the services that the specified pattern uses, and determines the node owner input that is required for them.
messages.translation: 針對可用於 'hzn register' 指令（一旦填寫）的這個型樣建立一個輸入檔範本。 這會檢查指定的型樣使用的服務並判定這些服務所需的節點擁有者輸入。

messages.id: The Horizon exchange node ID and token (it must already exist).
messages.message: The Horizon exchange node ID and token (it must already exist).
messages.translation: Horizon Exchange 節點 ID 和記號（必須存在）。

messages.id: The JSON input template file name that should be created. This file will contain placeholders for you to fill in user input values.
messages.message: The JSON input template file name that should be created. This file will contain placeholders for you to fill in user input values.
messages.translation: 應該建立的 JSON 輸入範本檔名。 此檔案將包含位置保留元供您填寫使用者輸入值。

messages.id: The Horizon exchange organization ID that the node will be registered in.
messages.message: The Horizon exchange organization ID that the node will be registered in.
messages.translation: 將在其中登錄節點的 Horizon Exchange 組織 ID。

messages.id: The Horizon exchange pattern that describes what workloads that should be deployed to this node. If the pattern is from a different organization than the node, use the 'other_org/pattern' format.
messages.message: The Horizon exchange pattern that describes what workloads that should be deployed to this node. If the pattern is from a different organization than the node, use the 'other_org/pattern' format.
messages.translation: 說明應該將哪些工作量部署至此節點的 Horizon Exchange 型樣。 如果型樣來自節點所在組織以外的組織，請使用 'other_org/pattern' 格式。

messages.id: The architecture to write the template file for. (Horizon ignores services in patterns whose architecture is different from the target system.) The architecture must be what is returned by 'hzn node list' on the target system.
messages.message: The architecture to write the template file for. (Horizon ignores services in patterns whose architecture is different from the target system.) The architecture must be what is returned by 'hzn node list' on the target system.
messages.translation: 要為其撰寫範本檔案的架構。 （Horizon 會忽略其架構不同於目標系統之型樣中的服務）。 架構必須是在目標系統上由 'hzn node list' 傳回的架構。

messages.id: Register this edge node with Horizon.
messages.message: Register this edge node with Horizon.
messages.translation: 使用 Horizon 登錄此邊緣節點。

messages.id: The Horizon exchange node ID and token. The node ID must be unique within the organization. If not specified, HZN_EXCHANGE_NODE_AUTH will be used as a default. If both -n and HZN_EXCHANGE_NODE_AUTH are not specified, the node ID will be created by Horizon from the machine serial number or fully qualified hostname. If the token is not specified, Horizon will create a random token. If node resource in the Exchange identified by the ID and token does not yet exist, you must also specify the -u flag so it can be created.
messages.message: The Horizon exchange node ID and token. The node ID must be unique within the organization. If not specified, HZN_EXCHANGE_NODE_AUTH will be used as a default. If both -n and HZN_EXCHANGE_NODE_AUTH are not specified, the node ID will be created by Horizon from the machine serial number or fully qualified hostname. If the token is not specified, Horizon will create a random token. If node resource in the Exchange identified by the ID and token does not yet exist, you must also specify the -u flag so it can be created.
messages.translation: Horizon Exchange 節點 ID 和記號。 節點 ID 在組織中必須是唯一的。 如果未指定，則將使用 HZN_EXCHANGE_NODE_AUTH 作為預設值。 如果未指定 -n 和 HZN_EXCHANGE_NODE_AUTH，則 Horizon 將根據機器序號或完整主機名稱來建立節點 ID。 如果未指定記號，則 Horizon 將建立一個隨機記號。 如果 Exchange 中由 ID 和記號識別的節點資源尚不存在，您還必須指定 -u 旗標以便建立節點資源。

messages.id: The name of the node. If not specified, it will be the same as the node id.
messages.message: The name of the node. If not specified, it will be the same as the node id.
messages.translation: 節點的名稱。 如果未指定，則將與節點 ID 相同。

messages.id: User credentials to create the node resource in the Horizon exchange if it does not already exist. If not specified, HZN_EXCHANGE_USER_AUTH will be used as a default.
messages.message: User credentials to create the node resource in the Horizon exchange if it does not already exist. If not specified, HZN_EXCHANGE_USER_AUTH will be used as a default.
messages.translation: 用來在 Horizon Exchange 中建立尚不存在的節點資源的使用者認證。 如果未指定，則將使用 HZN_EXCHANGE_USER_AUTH 作為預設值。

messages.id: A JSON file that sets or overrides user input variables needed by the services that will be deployed to this node. See {Sampledir}/user_input.json. Specify -f- to read from stdin.
messages.message: A JSON file that sets or overrides user input variables needed by the services that will be deployed to this node. See {Sampledir}/user_input.json. Specify -f- to read from stdin.
messages.translation: 用來設定或置換將部署至此節點之服務所需的使用者輸入變數的 JSON 檔案。 請參閱 {Sampledir}/user_input.json。 指定 -f- 以從 stdin 中讀取。

messages.id: The Horizon exchange organization ID that the node should be registered in. The default is the HZN_ORG_ID environment variable. Mutually exclusive with <nodeorg> and <pattern> arguments.
messages.message: The Horizon exchange organization ID that the node should be registered in. The default is the HZN_ORG_ID environment variable. Mutually exclusive with <nodeorg> and <pattern> arguments.
messages.translation: 應在其中登錄節點的 Horizon Exchange 組織 ID。 預設值是 HZN_ORG_ID 環境變數。 與 <nodeorg> 和 <pattern> 引數互斥。

messages.id: The Horizon exchange pattern that describes what workloads that should be deployed to this node. If the pattern is from a different organization than the node, use the 'other_org/pattern' format. Mutually exclusive with <nodeorg> and <pattern> arguments.
messages.message: The Horizon exchange pattern that describes what workloads that should be deployed to this node. If the pattern is from a different organization than the node, use the 'other_org/pattern' format. Mutually exclusive with <nodeorg> and <pattern> arguments.
messages.translation: 說明應該將哪些工作量部署至此節點的 Horizon Exchange 型樣。 如果型樣來自節點所在組織以外的組織，請使用 'other_org/pattern' 格式。 與 <nodeorg> 和 <pattern> 引數互斥。

messages.id: A JSON file that sets or overrides the node policy for this node that will be used for policy based agreement negotiation.
messages.message: A JSON file that sets or overrides the node policy for this node that will be used for policy based agreement negotiation.
messages.translation: 用來設定或置換此節點的節點原則（將用於原則型合約協議）的 JSON 檔案。

messages.id: The Horizon exchange organization ID that the node should be registered in. Mutually exclusive with -o and -p.
messages.message: The Horizon exchange organization ID that the node should be registered in. Mutually exclusive with -o and -p.
messages.translation: 應在其中登錄節點的 Horizon Exchange 組織 ID。 與 -o 和 -p 互斥。

messages.id: The Horizon exchange pattern that describes what workloads that should be deployed to this node. If the pattern is from a different organization than the node, use the 'other_org/pattern' format. Mutually exclusive with -o and -p.
messages.message: The Horizon exchange pattern that describes what workloads that should be deployed to this node. If the pattern is from a different organization than the node, use the 'other_org/pattern' format. Mutually exclusive with -o and -p.
messages.translation: 說明應該將哪些工作量部署至此節點的 Horizon Exchange 型樣。 如果型樣來自節點所在組織以外的組織，請使用 'other_org/pattern' 格式。 與 -o 和 -p 互斥。

messages.id: Wait for the named service to start executing on this node. When registering with a pattern, use '*' to watch all the services in the pattern. When registering with a policy, '*' is not a valid value for -s. This flag is not supported for edge cluster nodes.
messages.message: Wait for the named service to start executing on this node. When registering with a pattern, use '*' to watch all the services in the pattern. When registering with a policy, '*' is not a valid value for -s. This flag is not supported for edge cluster nodes.
messages.translation: 等待指名的服務在此節點上開始執行。 使用型樣登錄時，使用 '*' 以監看型樣中的所有服務。 使用原則登錄時，'*' 針對 -s 不是有效的值。 邊緣叢集節點不支援此旗標。

messages.id: The org of the service to wait for on this node. If '-s *' is specified, then --serviceorg must be omitted.
messages.message: The org of the service to wait for on this node. If '-s *' is specified, then --serviceorg must be omitted.
messages.translation: 要在此節點上等待之服務的組織。 如果指定 '-s *'，則必須省略 --serviceorg。

messages.id: The number of seconds for the --service to start. The default is 60 seconds, beginning when registration is successful. Ignored if --service is not specified.
messages.message: The number of seconds for the --service to start. The default is 60 seconds, beginning when registration is successful. Ignored if --service is not specified.
messages.translation: --service 啟動的秒數。 預設值是 60 秒，在登錄成功後開始。 如果未指定 --service，則予以忽略。

messages.id: List or manage the services that are currently registered on this Horizon edge node.
messages.message: List or manage the services that are currently registered on this Horizon edge node.
messages.translation: 列出或管理目前登錄在這個 Horizon 邊緣節點上的服務。

messages.id: List or manage the configuration state for the services that are currently registered on this Horizon edge node.
messages.message: List or manage the configuration state for the services that are currently registered on this Horizon edge node.
messages.translation: 列出或管理目前登錄在這個 Horizon 邊緣節點上的服務配置狀態。

messages.id: List the configuration state for the services that are currently registered on this Horizon edge node.
messages.message: List the configuration state for the services that are currently registered on this Horizon edge node.
messages.translation: 列出目前登錄在這個 Horizon 邊緣節點上的服務配置狀態。

messages.id: Change the configuration state to 'active' for a service.
messages.message: Change the configuration state to 'active' for a service.
messages.translation: 將服務的配置狀態變更為「作用中」。

messages.id: Resume all registerd services.
messages.message: Resume all registerd services.
messages.translation: 回復所有登錄服務。

messages.id: The organization of the service that should be resumed.
messages.message: The organization of the service that should be resumed.
messages.translation: 應該回復的服務的組織。

messages.id: The name of the service that should be resumed. If omitted, all the services for the organization will be resumed.
messages.message: The name of the service that should be resumed. If omitted, all the services for the organization will be resumed.
messages.translation: 應該回復的服務的名稱。 如果省略，系統將會回復組織的所有服務。

messages.id: The version of the service that should be resumed. If omitted, all the versions for this service will be resumed.
messages.message: The version of the service that should be resumed. If omitted, all the versions for this service will be resumed.
messages.translation: 應該回復之服務的版本。 如果省略，系統將會回復此服務的所有版本。

messages.id: Change the configuration state to 'suspend' for a service. Parent and child dependencies of the suspended service will be stopped until the service is resumed.
messages.message: Change the configuration state to 'suspend' for a service. Parent and child dependencies of the suspended service will be stopped until the service is resumed.
messages.translation: 將服務的配置狀態變更為「暫停」。 在回復已暫停的服務之前，系統將會停止該服務的母項和子項相依關係。

messages.id: Suspend all registerd services.
messages.message: Suspend all registerd services.
messages.translation: 暫停所有登錄服務。

messages.id: The organization of the service that should be suspended.
messages.message: The organization of the service that should be suspended.
messages.translation: 應該暫停的服務的組織。

messages.id: The name of the service that should be suspended. If omitted, all the services for the organization will be suspended.
messages.message: The name of the service that should be suspended. If omitted, all the services for the organization will be suspended.
messages.translation: 應該暫停的服務的名稱。 如果省略，系統將會暫停組織的所有服務。

messages.id: The version of the service that should be suspended. If omitted, all the versions for this service will be suspended.
messages.message: The version of the service that should be suspended. If omitted, all the versions for this service will be suspended.
messages.translation: 應該暫停之服務的版本。 如果省略，系統將會暫停此服務的所有版本。

messages.id: Show the container logs for a service.
messages.message: Show the container logs for a service.
messages.translation: 顯示服務的儲存器日誌。

messages.id: The name of the service whose log records should be displayed. The service name is the same as the url field of a service definition. Displays log records similar to tail behavior and returns .
messages.message: The name of the service whose log records should be displayed. The service name is the same as the url field of a service definition. Displays log records similar to tail behavior and returns .
messages.translation: 應顯示其日誌記錄的服務名稱。 服務名稱與服務定義的 URL 欄位相同。 顯示類似追蹤行為的日誌記錄並返回。

messages.id: The version of the service.
messages.message: The version of the service.
messages.translation: 服務的版本。

messages.id: The name of the container within the service whose log records should be displayed.
messages.message: The name of the container within the service whose log records should be displayed.
messages.translation: 應顯示其日誌記錄的服務內的儲存器名稱。

messages.id: List the services variable configuration that has been done on this Horizon edge node.
messages.message: List the services variable configuration that has been done on this Horizon edge node.
messages.translation: 列出已在這個 Horizon 邊緣節點上完成的服務變數配置。

messages.id: List the services that are currently registered on this Horizon edge node.
messages.message: List the services that are currently registered on this Horizon edge node.
messages.translation: 列出目前登錄在這個 Horizon 邊緣節點上的服務。

messages.id: Display the current horizon internal status for the node.
messages.message: Display the current horizon internal status for the node.
messages.translation: 顯示節點目前的 Horizon 內部狀態。

messages.id: Unregister and reset this Horizon edge node so that it is ready to be registered again. Warning: this will stop all the Horizon services running on this edge node, and restart the Horizon agent.
messages.message: Unregister and reset this Horizon edge node so that it is ready to be registered again. Warning: this will stop all the Horizon services running on this edge node, and restart the Horizon agent.
messages.translation: 取消登錄並重設這個 Horizon 邊緣節點以便備妥進行重新登錄。 警告：這樣做將會停止在此邊緣節點上執行的所有 Horizon 服務，然後重新啟動 Horizon 代理程式。

messages.id: Also remove this node resource from the Horizon exchange (because you no longer want to use this node with Horizon).
messages.message: Also remove this node resource from the Horizon exchange (because you no longer want to use this node with Horizon).
messages.translation: 此外，還會從 Horizon Exchange 中移除這個節點資源（因為您不再想要將此節點與 Horizon 搭配使用）。

messages.id: Also remove all the previous registration information. Use it only after the 'hzn unregister' command failed. Please capture the logs by running 'hzn eventlog list -a -l' command before using this flag.
messages.message: Also remove all the previous registration information. Use it only after the 'hzn unregister' command failed. Please capture the logs by running 'hzn eventlog list -a -l' command before using this flag.
messages.translation: 還會移除所有先前的登錄資訊。 僅在 'hzn unregister' 指令失敗之後使用它。 請在使用此旗標之前透過執行 'hzn eventlog list -a -l' 指令來擷取日誌。

messages.id: The number of minutes to wait for unregistration to complete. The default is zero which will wait forever.
messages.message: The number of minutes to wait for unregistration to complete. The default is zero which will wait forever.
messages.translation: 等待完成取消註冊的分鐘數。 預設值是零，表示永遠等待。

messages.id: List or manage the service user inputs that are currently registered on this Horizon edge node.
messages.message: List or manage the service user inputs that are currently registered on this Horizon edge node.
messages.translation: 列出或管理目前登錄在這個 Horizon 邊緣節點上的服務使用者輸入。

messages.id: Add a new user input object or overwrite the current user input object for this Horizon edge node.
messages.message: Add a new user input object or overwrite the current user input object for this Horizon edge node.
messages.translation: 針對此 Horizon 邊緣節點新增新的使用者輸入物件或改寫現行使用者輸入物件。

messages.id: The file path to the json file with the user input object. Specify -f- to read from stdin.
messages.message: The file path to the json file with the user input object. Specify -f- to read from stdin.
messages.translation: 包含使用者輸入物件之 JSON 檔案的檔案路徑。 指定 -f- 以從 stdin 中讀取。

messages.id: List the service user inputs currently registered on this Horizon edge node.
messages.message: List the service user inputs currently registered on this Horizon edge node.
messages.translation: 列出目前登錄在這個 Horizon 邊緣節點上的服務使用者輸入。

messages.id: Display an empty userinput template.
messages.message: Display an empty userinput template.
messages.translation: 顯示空使用者輸入範本。

messages.id: Remove the user inputs that are currently registered on this Horizon edge node.
messages.message: Remove the user inputs that are currently registered on this Horizon edge node.
messages.translation: 移除目前登錄在這個 Horizon 邊緣節點上的使用者輸入。

messages.id: Skip the 'Are you sure?' prompt.
messages.message: Skip the 'Are you sure?' prompt.
messages.translation: 跳過「確定嗎？」 提示。

messages.id: Update an existing user input object for this Horizon edge node.
messages.message: Update an existing user input object for this Horizon edge node.
messages.translation: 更新這個 Horizon 邊緣節點的現有使用者輸入物件。

messages.id: The file path to the json file with the updated user input object. Specify -f- to read from stdin.
messages.message: The file path to the json file with the updated user input object. Specify -f- to read from stdin.
messages.translation: 包含已更新使用者輸入物件之 JSON 檔案的檔案路徑。 指定 -f- 以從 stdin 中讀取。

messages.id: Utility commands.
messages.message: Utility commands.
messages.translation: 公用程式指令。

messages.id: Convert the configuration file from JSON format to a shell script.
messages.message: Convert the configuration file from JSON format to a shell script.
messages.translation: 將配置檔從 JSON 格式轉換為 Shell Script。

messages.id: The path of a configuration file to be converted.
messages.message: The path of a configuration file to be converted.
messages.translation: 要轉換之配置檔的路徑。

messages.id: Sign the text in stdin. The signature is sent to stdout.
messages.message: Sign the text in stdin. The signature is sent to stdout.
messages.translation: 簽署 stdin 中的文字。 簽章將傳送至 stdout。

messages.id: The path of a private key file to be used to sign the stdin.
messages.message: The path of a private key file to be used to sign the stdin.
messages.translation: 用來簽署 stdin 之私密金鑰檔的路徑。

messages.id: Verify that the signature specified via -s is a valid signature for the text in stdin.
messages.message: Verify that the signature specified via -s is a valid signature for the text in stdin.
messages.translation: 驗證透過 -s 指定的簽章是否是 stdin 中的文字的有效簽章。

messages.id: The path of public key file (that corresponds to the private key that was used to sign) to verify the signature of stdin.
messages.message: The path of public key file (that corresponds to the private key that was used to sign) to verify the signature of stdin.
messages.translation: 用來驗證 stdin 簽章之公開金鑰檔（對應於用來簽署的私密金鑰）的路徑。

messages.id: The supposed signature of stdin.
messages.message: The supposed signature of stdin.
messages.translation: stdin 的假定簽章。

messages.id: List and manage secrets in the secrets manager. NOTE: You must authenticate as an administrator to list secrets available to the entire organization.
messages.message: List and manage secrets in the secrets manager. NOTE: You must authenticate as an administrator to list secrets available to the entire organization.
messages.translation: 列出並管理密碼管理程式中的密碼。 附註：您必須以管理者身分進行鑑別，才能列出可供整個組織使用的密碼。

messages.id: Horizon Exchange credentials to query secrets manager resources. The default is HZN_EXCHANGE_USER_AUTH environment variable. If you don't prepend it with the user's org, it will automatically be prepended with the value of the HZN_ORG_ID environment variable.
messages.message: Horizon Exchange credentials to query secrets manager resources. The default is HZN_EXCHANGE_USER_AUTH environment variable. If you don't prepend it with the user's org, it will automatically be prepended with the value of the HZN_ORG_ID environment variable.
messages.translation: 用於查詢密碼管理程式資源的 Horizon Exchange 認證。 預設值是 HZN_EXCHANGE_USER_AUTH 環境變數。 如果您未在它前面加上使用者的組織，則它前面會自動加上 HZN_ORG_ID 環境變數的值。

messages.id: List and manage secrets in the secrets manager.
messages.message: List and manage secrets in the secrets manager.
messages.translation: 列出並管理密碼管理程式中的密碼。

messages.id: Display the names of the secrets in the secrets manager.
messages.message: Display the names of the secrets in the secrets manager.
messages.translation: 顯示密碼管理程式中的密碼名稱。

messages.id: List just this one secret. Returns a boolean indicating the existence of the secret. This is the name of the secret used in the secrets manager. If the secret does not exist, returns with exit code 1.
messages.message: List just this one secret. Returns a boolean indicating the existence of the secret. This is the name of the secret used in the secrets manager. If the secret does not exist, returns with exit code 1.
messages.translation: 僅列出這一個密碼。 傳回一個布林值，指出密碼存在。 這是密碼管理程式中使用的密碼名稱。 如果密碼不存在，則傳回結束碼 1。

messages.id: Add a secret to the secrets manager.
messages.message: Add a secret to the secrets manager.
messages.translation: 將密碼新增至密碼管理程式。

messages.id: The name of the secret. It must be unique within your organization. This name is used in deployment policies and patterns to bind this secret to a secret name in a service definition.
messages.message: The name of the secret. It must be unique within your organization. This name is used in deployment policies and patterns to bind this secret to a secret name in a service definition.
messages.translation: 密碼的名稱。 它在您的組織內必須是唯一的。 在部署原則和型樣中使用此名稱，以將此密碼連結至服務定義中的密碼名稱。

messages.id: Filepath to a file containing the secret details. Mutually exclusive with --secretDetail. Specify -f- to read from stdin.

messages.id:
Cannot proceed with the given pattern {Pattern} because it is different from the pattern {ExchangePattern} defined for the node in the Exchange.
To correct the problem, please do one of the following: 
	- Remove the node from the Exchange 
	- Remove the pattern from the node in the Exchange 
	- Register without a pattern (the pattern defined on the node in the Exchange will be used)
messages.message:
Cannot proceed with the given pattern {Pattern} because it is different from the pattern {ExchangePattern} defined for the node in the Exchange.
To correct the problem, please do one of the following: 
	- Remove the node from the Exchange 
	- Remove the pattern from the node in the Exchange 
	- Register without a pattern (the pattern defined on the node in the Exchange will be used)
messages.translation:
無法繼續使用給定的型樣 {Pattern}，因為它與為 Exchange 中節點定義的型樣 {ExchangePattern} 不同。
若要更正問題，請執行下列其中一項：
	- 從 Exchange 中移除節點 
	- 從 Exchange 的節點中移除型樣 
	- 在沒有型樣的情況下進行登錄（將使用在 Exchange 中節點上定義的型樣）

messages.translation: 正在列出組織 {Org} 中的物件：

messages.id: Required: A unique identifier of the object.
messages.message: Required: A unique identifier of the object.
messages.translation: 必需：物件的唯一 ID。

messages.id: Required: The type of the object.
messages.message: Required: The type of the object.
messages.translation: 必需：物件的類型。

messages.id: Required: The organization ID of the object (an object belongs to exactly one organization).
messages.message: Required: The organization ID of the object (an object belongs to exactly one organization).
messages.translation: 必需：物件的組織 ID（一個物件只屬於一個組織）。

messages.id: The node id (without org prefix) where the object should be placed.
messages.message: The node id (without org prefix) where the object should be placed.
messages.translation: 應用來放置物件的節點 ID（不含組織字首）。

messages.id: If omitted the object is sent to all nodes with the same destinationType.
messages.message: If omitted the object is sent to all nodes with the same destinationType.
messages.translation: 省略的話，物件會傳送至具有同一目的地類型的所有節點。

messages.id: Delete this field when you are using destinationPolicy.
messages.message: Delete this field when you are using destinationPolicy.
messages.translation: 在使用目的地原則時刪除此欄位。

messages.id: The pattern in use by nodes that should receive this object.
messages.message: The pattern in use by nodes that should receive this object.
messages.translation: 型樣正由應該接收此物件的節點使用。

messages.id: If omitted (and if destinationsList is omitted too) the object is broadcast to all known nodes.
messages.message: If omitted (and if destinationsList is omitted too) the object is broadcast to all known nodes.
messages.translation: 省略的話（同時省略目的地清單），物件會播送至所有已知節點。

messages.id: Delete this field when you are using policy.
messages.message: Delete this field when you are using policy.
messages.translation: 在使用原則時刪除此欄位。

messages.id: The list of destinations as an array of pattern:nodeId pairs that should receive this object.
messages.message: The list of destinations as an array of pattern:nodeId pairs that should receive this object.
messages.translation: 作為應接收此物件之 pattern:nodeId 配對陣列的目的地清單。

messages.id: If provided, destinationType and destinationID must be omitted.
messages.message: If provided, destinationType and destinationID must be omitted.
messages.translation: 提供的話，必須省略目的地類型和目的地 ID。

messages.id: The policy specification that should be used to distribute this object.
messages.message: The policy specification that should be used to distribute this object.
messages.translation: 應該用來配送此物件的原則規範。

messages.id: Delete these fields if the target node is using a pattern.
messages.message: Delete these fields if the target node is using a pattern.
messages.translation: 當目標節點正在使用型樣時刪除這些欄位。

messages.id: Valid types are string, bool, int, float, list of strings (comma separated), version.
messages.message: Valid types are string, bool, int, float, list of strings (comma separated), version.
messages.translation: 有效類型是字串、布林、整數、浮點數、字串清單（以逗點分隔）、版本。

messages.id: Type can be omitted if the type is discernable from the value, e.g. unquoted true is boolean.
messages.message: Type can be omitted if the type is discernable from the value, e.g. unquoted true is boolean.
messages.translation: 如果類型可與值區別（例如，true 不加引號表示布林），則可以省略類型。

messages.id: A list of constraint expressions of the form <property name> <operator> <property value>, separated by boolean operators AND (&&) or OR (||).
messages.message: A list of constraint expressions of the form <property name> <operator> <property value>, separated by boolean operators AND (&&) or OR (||).
messages.translation: 格式為 <property name> <operator> <property value> 的限制項表示式清單，以布林運算子 AND (&&) 或 OR (||) 分隔。

messages.id: The service(s) that will use this object.
messages.message: The service(s) that will use this object.
messages.translation: 將使用此物件的服務。

messages.id: Set to '*' to indcate services of any hardware architecture.
messages.message: Set to '*' to indcate services of any hardware architecture.
messages.translation: 設為 '*' 表示任何硬體架構的服務。

messages.id: A version range.
messages.message: A version range.
messages.translation: 版本範圍。

messages.id: A timestamp/date indicating when the object expires (it is automatically deleted). The timestamp should be provided in RFC3339 format.
messages.message: A timestamp/date indicating when the object expires (it is automatically deleted). The timestamp should be provided in RFC3339 format.
messages.translation: 時間戳記/日期表示物件的到期日（系統會自動將它刪除）。 應該以 RFC3339 格式提供時間戳記。

messages.id: Arbitrary string value. The value is not semantically interpreted. The Model Management System does not keep multiple version of an object.
messages.message: Arbitrary string value. The value is not semantically interpreted. The Model Management System does not keep multiple version of an object.
messages.translation: 任意字串值。 該值沒有語義解譯。 「模型管理系統」不會保留物件的多個版本。

messages.id: An arbitrary description.
messages.message: An arbitrary description.
messages.translation: 任意說明。

messages.id: A timestamp/date as to when this object should automatically be activated. The timestamp should be provided in RFC3339 format.
messages.message: A timestamp/date as to when this object should automatically be activated. The timestamp should be provided in RFC3339 format.
messages.translation: 時間戳記/日期指出何時應自動啟動此物件。 應該以 RFC3339 格式提供時間戳記。
